superadmins.name: brussels
superadmins.bio: Server co-founder, I also admin the codecademy subreddit and forums. In my spare time, I enjoy working absurdly late hours and cross country running.

mods.name: 8-Bit
mods.bio: Texas rancher, hobbyist programmer, occasional writer, and martial artist. I'm a moderator for the Codecademy Discord and a super user on their forums. I seek to learn and help out others were I can along the way.

mods.name: Codeneutrino [AUS CL]
mods.bio: Hobbyist programmer who enjoys maths and science, and also a pretty awful pianist. I'm a mod on Discord, but I'm also a Super User on the forums.

cocos.name: megara | Rachel (she/her)
cocos.bio: I'm Rachel, and after working in journalism for almost 20 years I decided to make the switch to coding. I now work as a solutions engineer, but you'll still find me hanging around the CodeCademy discord. I like answering folks' questions â€” and I still have plenty to learn myself. In my spare time I like video games, sewing, and cooking.

cocos.name: Alex Wojtak (he/him)
cocos.bio: I'm Alex, and after being a Scientific Instrumentation Engineer for about 20 years, I decided to dive fully into coding as a new career using the codecademy platform to learn. I'm often found on the codecademy discord, and I'm most comfortable with Full Stack development, but I've also coded in Python, Java, C#, and a bunch of other languages too! I love helping people with their questions, and learning new things.

cocos.name: Hunter The Milk Turtle
cocos.bio: My name's Hunter, I'm a college student majoring in computer science and I'm a code counselor on the discord server. My main language is python although I have experience with several other languages, and I am always excited to learn anything new no matter how hard it may be at first. I enjoy helping beginners learn coding and helping anyone with any issues they may have even if I don't know the exact solution myself.
